# File-based routing (TanStack Router)

## Dot notation = parent + child

In `src/routes/`, a dot in the filename nests the route under the segment before the dot:

- `account.tsx` → `/account` (parent)
- `account.edit.tsx` → `/account/edit` (child of `account`)
- `lines.$lineId.edit.tsx` → `/lines/$lineId/edit` (child of `lines.$lineId`)

Regenerate types after adding routes: `pnpm generate-routes`.

## Parent routes must render `<Outlet />`

If a route has child routes, the parent component **must** render `<Outlet />`. Without it,
navigation to the child URL succeeds but the child page never appears — the parent UI stays
visible (e.g. clicking "Edit profile" on `/account` and remaining on the account page).

## Page content belongs in `*.index.tsx`

When a segment has sub-routes, split it into three files:

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `foo.tsx` | Layout only — `return <Outlet />` |
| `foo.index.tsx` | Default page at `/foo` |
| `foo.edit.tsx` | Child page at `/foo/edit` |

Canonical examples in this repo:

- `lines.$lineId.tsx` + `lines.$lineId.index.tsx` + `lines.$lineId.edit.tsx`
- `account.tsx` + `account.index.tsx` + `account.edit.tsx`

Do **not** put full page UI in a parent route file that also has dot-suffixed siblings.

## Leaf routes (no children)

Routes with no dot-suffixed siblings can be a single file with full page content
(e.g. `search.tsx`, `lines.new.tsx`).

## Links

Use the public path in `<Link to="...">` (e.g. `to="/account/edit"`), not the file id
(`/_authenticated/account/edit`).
